titles.short: Big in Japan
titles.full: Big in Japan

summaries.short: Ben and Cam get hooked up with a top Japanese buyer, but find their business taking a surprising detour.
summaries.full: After running into a designer, Ben and Cam get hooked up with a top Japanese buyer named Hidemi, but find their business taking a surprising detour. Meanwhile, Rene runs into some unexpected problems locating a pile of stashed cash; and Rachel, hoping to bring some fresh energy into her relationship with Darren, is flummoxed by his euphoric reaction to the party drug Ecstasy.

titles.short: Good Vintage
titles.full: Good Vintage

summaries.short: Ben and Cam find it hard to meet Hidemi's vintage-tee quota of 300 until an attractive retail employee named Julie helps bail them out.
summaries.full: Ben and Cam find it hard to meet Hidemi's vintage-tee quota of 300--until an attractive retail employee named Julie helps bail them out. Rene gets some fatherly advice on how to handle an impending schoolyard showdown. Rachel's trip to Connecticut to check on a behind-schedule carpenter ends with Darren taking her to meet his mother--and asking a big question.

titles.short: Unhappy Birthday
titles.full: Unhappy Birthday

summaries.short: Trying to escape the fact that it's Rachel's birthday, Ben spends the night taking Kaplan to a velvet-rope nightclub.
summaries.full: In an attempt to divert himself from the depressing fact that it's Rachel's birthday and she's being thrown an intimate dinner party, Ben decides to spend the night taking Kaplan to a velvet-rope nightclub. Meanwhile, Cam lands a lucrative gig bartending at a gala benefit, but decides to forfeit the job to keep a forlorn Ben--and Kaplan and Domingo--company.

titles.short: Keep on Truck'n
titles.full: Keep on Truck'n

summaries.short: While Ben is getting tight with Julie, Rachel is put off by Darren's offer; Rene's big meeting with John Lardner gets an unexpected guest.
summaries.full: While Ben is getting tight with Julie, Rachel is put off by Darren's sudden offer to let her and Edie design a hotel. Meanwhile, Cam and Ben agree to hand out Rasta Monsta samples at Union Square; Rene agrees to meet with John Lardner, the Jamaica-based owner of Rasta Monsta, about taking over North American distribution rights to the drink.

titles.short: Paper, Denim + Dollars
titles.full: Paper, Denim + Dollars

summaries.short: Ben and Cam track down a tailor to re-imagine some 1970s-era jeans; and Rachel rethinks her future.
summaries.full: While Ben and Cam track down a tailor to re-imagine some 1970s-era jeans, Rachel rethinks her future. Eager to get a bigger marketing commitment for his fledgling "Rasta Monsta" drink, Rene makes a buyout offer his marketing partners better not refuse. Later, Cam and Ben round up money to pay the tailor, deliver the denim, and launch 'Crisp NYC.'

titles.short: Never Say Die
titles.full: Never Say Die

summaries.short: In the Season One finale, Cam suspects Rene in the disappearance of his and Ben's tees; Rachel makes a life choice.
summaries.full: In the Season One finale, Cam suspects Rene of having something to do with the theft of the Rasta Monsta truck filled with his and Ben's Crisp tees--but is he man enough to confront his hot-tempered cousin? Meanwhile, Rachel makes a decision that impacts the lives of Ben, Edie and Darren.

titles.short: Crisp
titles.full: Crisp

summaries.short: Ben and Cam borrow more money from Rene in an effort to launch a line of retro-70s jeans.
summaries.full: Using a $3G loan from Rene, Ben and Cam buy up a roll of (hot) premium-denim material, then hit a series of dead ends in their search to find a manufacturer to make samples of their 'Crisp' brand of retro-70s jeans. Meanwhile, both Ben and Rachel realize that they haven't totally 'moved on,' and vow to try harder in the future.
